com.orchestranetworks.workflow
Interface ProcessInstanceStep

public interface ProcessInstanceStep

Represents a step of a process instance. A workflow step can be:

  • a script task,
  • a condition,
  • a user task,
  • a sub-workflows invocation.

Since:
5.4.1
See Also:
ProcessInstanceHistory

getSubWorkflowsInvocationSubWorkflows

List getSubWorkflowsInvocationSubWorkflows()
Returns the list of sub-workflows associated with this sub-workflow invocation step; returns null if this step is not a sub-workflow invocation.

To get the history of a sub workflow, uses WorkflowEngine.getProcessInstanceHistory(ProcessInstanceKey) with the key of the sub-workflow.

Returns:
a List of ProcessInstance.
Since:
5.5.0
